03:13.960 --> 03:16.630
as big as the copied image.

03:16.630 --> 03:23.030
So I'm going to zoom out a bit with the minus key on the keyboard here and there it is.

03:23.110 --> 03:30.880
So I will call this front view and let's go back and get the side view.

03:31.000 --> 03:33.270
So I'll come back over here.

03:33.280 --> 03:43.160
Hide the front view turn on the side view select it and then I'll go to edit copy and then I'll come

03:43.160 --> 03:50.200
back over here to this new image and go to Edit Paste.

03:50.350 --> 03:57.780
And there he is now in GIMP when you paste a layer where you paste an image into a document.

03:57.940 --> 04:01.430
It gives you this floating selection pasted layer.

04:01.720 --> 04:07.090
And what that is it's kind of a temporary layer and you have to anchor it to something so you could

04:07.120 --> 04:10.110
anchor it to this existing layer.

04:10.390 --> 04:13.310
Or you could create a new layer for it to be anchored to.

04:13.510 --> 04:17.150
I don't want to combine it with this when I want to keep them separate.

04:17.230 --> 04:22.480
So what I'll do is all right click on this and choose two new layer.

04:22.480 --> 04:26.660
And now that will give that its own layer in the document.

04:26.920 --> 04:29.520
So I call this side view.

04:30.430 --> 04:37.300
So now I have my front view and my side view ready to be saved out.

04:37.300 --> 04:41.340
And one thing I want to do is make sure that they're aligned properly.

04:41.350 --> 04:50.440
I want the feet and the eyes and the nose et cetera to be lined up between the side view and the front

04:50.440 --> 04:51.580
view.

04:51.580 --> 04:56.070
So what I'm going to do is turn the opacity down here I'm going to click.

04:56.080 --> 05:01.630
I'm going to hover right over here and the opacity and drag this down some so that I can see through

05:01.630 --> 05:08.170
that side view and you can see the eyes were a little bit off so I'm going to zoom in and click out

05:08.170 --> 05:13.500
here and press the Z key and click and drag here to zoom in and then I'm going to come over here to

05:13.590 --> 05:16.640
move to all or the AM key.

05:16.720 --> 05:26.530
I'm just going to take the arrow keys on the keyboard and move it over so that the nose and the eyes

05:26.530 --> 05:32.980
