06:22.400 --> 06:25.280
So now I know that they're pretty well lined up.

06:25.280 --> 06:29.070
I mean you can see that the belt isn't quite right.

06:29.210 --> 06:30.930
The feet are pretty good.

06:30.980 --> 06:36.060
Of course the hands and the arms are separate pieces in the drawing.

06:36.380 --> 06:43.160
But it looks to me like the eyes and the nose are lined up and at least for me for now that's kind of

06:43.160 --> 06:44.980
my main concern.

06:44.990 --> 06:45.680
All right.

06:45.830 --> 06:52.910
So now that I have these lined up I'm going to hide one of the layers here so I'll just deal with the

06:53.150 --> 06:54.610
front view.

06:54.620 --> 07:01.220
So now what I'm going to do is save these images out so that I can bring them into blender as reference

07:01.220 --> 07:02.150
